definitions.definition: A marine mollusc , of the family Nautilidae native to the Pacific Ocean and Indian Ocean , which has tentacles and a spiral shell with a series of air-filled chambers, of which Nautilus is the type genus.
A kind of diving bell that sinks or rises by means of compressed air .

main_definition: A marine mollusc , of the family Nautilidae native to the Pacific Ocean and Indian Ocean , which has tentacles and a spiral shell with a series of air-filled chambers, of which Nautilus is the type genus.
